job_text:
As a Data Scientist, you will develop and deliver innovative and comprehensive insights, undertake complex analysis, and implement advanced analytical capabilities that enable Aurizon to achieve it’s strategic, operational, and commercial objectives.

You will be a valued member of the Data Science team within the Data Reporting and Analytics section of Aurizon’s Technology division.

About the role:

    Provide expertise in quantitative (statistical and mathematical) analysis and advanced machine learning methods (data mining, pattern detection, simulation, predictive modelling, and deep learning)
    Partner with business units to identify strategic and operational process improvements
    Advise, guide, and manage the delivery of value adding data science projects and initiatives
    Prototype, develop, manage, update, and maintain complex analytical models, processes, frameworks, and tools
    Use cutting-edge analytical capabilities and complex data analysis to generate sophisticated data insights
    Provide guidance on the acquisition, integration, retention, and publication of data incorporating business requirements and knowledge of best practice

About you:

    Degree in operations research, applied statistics, mathematics, computer science, physics, engineering or a related quantitative discipline.
    Experience in designing and implementing applied statistical, mathematical, data mining, and machine learning solutions on complex and diverse data sets using language systems and tools
    Experience in developing scalable analytics solutions by using big data and analytics services in major on-premise and cloud platforms
    Experience in designing, testing, and validating complex experiments, scenario modelling, and hypotheses to qualify and validate findings
    Polished and professional communication with the ability to translate complex technical information into user-friendly business terms
    Balance innovation, risk, and practicality when assessing new ideas
    A curious self-starter
